Installing BANDIT on the HOST system
====================================

Download the latest version of the bandit from phyglos.org
$ wget ftp://phyglos.org/bandit/bandit 
$ tar xvf bandit
$ mv bandit-x.y.z bandit

As root, move the file to /opt and change into that directory
# mv bandit /opt
# cd /opt
# chown -R root.root /opt/bandit

Initialize the HOST environment for BANDIT from the bandit home directory:
# cd bandit
# source bin/bandit-set

Bandit should work now in the HOST. Test with:
# bandit --version

Read the file RAISE to learn how to use the BANDIT to raise a new TARGET system.


